WEBVTT

00:00:01.146 --> 00:00:03.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:06.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there a connection, a relationship,

00:00:06.569 --> 00:00:09.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
between love and peace?

00:00:11.031 --> 00:00:14.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if so, what role does love play

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:17.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
in achieving genuine peace?

00:00:18.497 --> 00:00:21.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible helps us to appreciate

00:00:21.166 --> 00:00:25.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
that love is an essential element

00:00:25.212 --> 00:00:28.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
in achieving genuine peace.

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:32.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we’re interested in showing love.

00:00:34.263 --> 00:00:37.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
As students of the Bible, we know

00:00:37.016 --> 00:00:39.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
that humans were created
in the image of God.

00:00:39.894 --> 00:00:44.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as a result,
you and I have the ability to show love.

00:00:45.941 --> 00:00:48.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we also know that we live in a world

00:00:48.193 --> 00:00:51.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
that has a very distorted view

00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:53.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
and definition of love.

00:00:53.782 --> 00:00:56.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
That, combined with our own imperfection,

00:00:56.785 --> 00:00:59.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
means that if we’re not careful,

00:00:59.163 --> 00:01:02.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
our view of love can become distorted.

00:01:04.001 --> 00:01:06.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how do we guard against that?

00:01:07.796 --> 00:01:12.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
By allowing Jehovah to teach us how to love.

00:01:13.886 --> 00:01:18.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when you think about it,
what better teacher could we have?

00:01:18.891 --> 00:01:22.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible says that “God is love.”

00:01:22.603 --> 00:01:25.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
That means that Jehovah, our Creator

00:01:25.397 --> 00:01:29.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
—who knows us better than we know ourselves,

00:01:29.109 --> 00:01:32.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
who embodies, who personifies love—

00:01:32.696 --> 00:01:36.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
is willing to teach us how to love.

00:01:36.909 --> 00:01:38.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how does he do that?

00:01:38.953 --> 00:01:42.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, by means of his Word, the Bible,

00:01:42.831 --> 00:01:46.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
and by means of his own beautiful example.

00:01:46.335 --> 00:01:49.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we get acquainted with Jehovah,

00:01:49.088 --> 00:01:52.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
we learn what love really is.

00:01:52.383 --> 00:01:55.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as we put that love to work,

00:01:55.928 --> 00:01:58.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
as Jesus did,

00:01:58.180 --> 00:02:00.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
then we’re in a position

00:02:00.849 --> 00:02:03.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
to enjoy genuine peace.

00:02:04.979 --> 00:02:06.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this symposium,

00:02:06.981 --> 00:02:11.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to explore how love for God,

00:02:11.235 --> 00:02:13.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
love of neighbor,

00:02:13.237 --> 00:02:16.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
and love for God’s Word, the Bible,

00:02:16.031 --> 00:02:19.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
can lead to genuine peace.

00:02:19.576 --> 00:02:23.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, let’s talk about love for God.

00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:26.500 line:90% position:50% align:center
How important is that

00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:30.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we want to enjoy genuine peace?

00:02:30.379 --> 00:02:33.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, Jesus provides some insight
in a statement he made

00:02:33.757 --> 00:02:37.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s recorded in our Bibles
at Matthew chapter 22.

00:02:37.011 --> 00:02:38.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look at it.

00:02:38.345 --> 00:02:40.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew chapter 22,

00:02:40.431 --> 00:02:43.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re going to read verse 37.

00:02:45.102 --> 00:02:49.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, to provide some context for these words,

00:02:49.648 --> 00:02:52.609 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus has been asked a question by a man

00:02:52.609 --> 00:02:55.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
who is well-versed in the Law.

00:02:55.320 --> 00:02:59.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[What] is the greatest commandment
in the Law?”

00:02:59.783 --> 00:03:03.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice how Jesus responds:

00:03:03.162 --> 00:03:05.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He said to him:

00:03:05.539 --> 00:03:08.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘You must love Jehovah your God

00:03:08.834 --> 00:03:10.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘with your whole heart

00:03:10.836 --> 00:03:13.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and with your whole soul

00:03:13.213 --> 00:03:16.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and with your whole mind.’

00:03:16.008 --> 00:03:20.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is the greatest and first commandment.”

00:03:21.513 --> 00:03:26.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You must love Jehovah your God”
—a command.

00:03:28.228 --> 00:03:30.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
Love for Jehovah is essential.

00:03:30.689 --> 00:03:34.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has to be
the most important relationship in our life.

00:03:34.985 --> 00:03:37.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
More important than any human,

00:03:37.696 --> 00:03:40.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
more important than any thing

00:03:40.824 --> 00:03:43.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
—we want to love Jehovah.

00:03:43.285 --> 00:03:45.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
To what extent?

00:03:45.079 --> 00:03:49.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, Jesus says: “with your whole heart.”

00:03:49.708 --> 00:03:52.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
What does that involve?

00:03:52.086 --> 00:03:54.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
The context of Jesus’ words

00:03:54.963 --> 00:03:59.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
helps us to understand that he was talking
about a person’s feelings,

00:03:59.718 --> 00:04:02.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
emotions, desires.

00:04:02.763 --> 00:04:07.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
So does love for God involve our emotions?

00:04:07.226 --> 00:04:09.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absolutely!

00:04:09.478 --> 00:04:14.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it has to involve more
than a simple affection for God.

00:04:14.274 --> 00:04:15.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why do we say that?

00:04:15.901 --> 00:04:19.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what did Jesus say next?

00:04:19.154 --> 00:04:21.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With your whole soul,”

00:04:21.323 --> 00:04:24.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is, with your entire being.

00:04:24.409 --> 00:04:27.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
We use everything we have

00:04:27.204 --> 00:04:29.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
to praise Jehovah

00:04:29.373 --> 00:04:32.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to prove our love for him.

00:04:33.460 --> 00:04:35.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
But even more is involved.

00:04:35.921 --> 00:04:38.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus concludes by saying:

00:04:38.173 --> 00:04:41.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
“with your whole mind.”

00:04:41.301 --> 00:04:45.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
So our intellectual faculties are involved.

00:04:45.055 --> 00:04:47.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re willing to take the time

00:04:47.641 --> 00:04:50.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get to know Jehovah’s thinking

00:04:50.853 --> 00:04:53.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
and make it our thinking.

00:04:53.438 --> 00:04:56.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to think the way Jehovah thinks.

00:04:56.483 --> 00:04:59.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to understand his purpose

00:04:59.611 --> 00:05:03.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his requirements for us,

00:05:03.574 --> 00:05:06.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we want to understand his personality.

00:05:08.203 --> 00:05:12.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, when we think about that kind of love,

00:05:12.749 --> 00:05:16.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s clear that it encompasses

00:05:16.336 --> 00:05:20.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
our thoughts, our words, and our actions.

00:05:20.966 --> 00:05:24.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nothing is left out.

00:05:24.386 --> 00:05:26.972 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that kind of love

00:05:26.972 --> 00:05:31.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
provides a basis for a friendship with God.

00:05:32.394 --> 00:05:37.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that results in peace with God.

00:05:37.024 --> 00:05:40.485 line:90% position:50% align:center
So there we see the progression.

00:05:40.485 --> 00:05:43.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
Loving Jehovah with our whole heart,

00:05:43.864 --> 00:05:46.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
soul, and mind

00:05:46.992 --> 00:05:50.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
leads to peace with God.

00:05:50.204 --> 00:05:53.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as we enjoy peace with God,

00:05:53.165 --> 00:05:55.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can also enjoy inner peace

00:05:55.918 --> 00:05:59.838 line:90% position:50% align:center
and peace with those around us.

00:05:59.838 --> 00:06:02.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, how does that work?

00:06:02.090 --> 00:06:06.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, our love for Jehovah
motivates us to imitate him,

00:06:06.637 --> 00:06:10.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we cultivate the qualities

00:06:10.474 --> 00:06:13.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah displays,

00:06:13.268 --> 00:06:16.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
for example: patience,

00:06:16.063 --> 00:06:19.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
kindness, mildness

00:06:19.733 --> 00:06:23.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
—qualities that make us attractive to others,

00:06:23.445 --> 00:06:27.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
and qualities that promote peace with others.

00:06:29.701 --> 00:06:31.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sure you would agree

00:06:31.828 --> 00:06:35.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we want to be at peace with God.

00:06:37.209 --> 00:06:41.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
But sometimes our peace can be threatened.

00:06:41.672 --> 00:06:44.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may experience pressure.

00:06:44.508 --> 00:06:48.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may be the subject of some wrong,

00:06:48.595 --> 00:06:52.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
some injustice, some evil

00:06:52.724 --> 00:06:56.812 line:90% position:50% align:center
that threatens our peace.

00:06:56.812 --> 00:06:59.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then the question is this:

00:06:59.606 --> 00:07:02.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
Will we handle things in a way

00:07:02.150 --> 00:07:04.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is pleasing to Jehovah

00:07:04.861 --> 00:07:07.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
or will we become impatient

00:07:07.030 --> 00:07:10.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
