00:11:46.726 --> 00:11:48.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
and verse 23:

00:11:51.398 --> 00:11:54.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
“After they had inflicted many blows on them,

00:11:56.653 --> 00:11:58.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
“they threw them into prison

00:12:00.824 --> 00:12:04.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and ordered the jailer
to guard them securely.

00:12:06.746 --> 00:12:09.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Because he got such an order, he threw them

00:12:09.457 --> 00:12:11.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
“into the inner prison

00:12:11.459 --> 00:12:14.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and fastened their feet in the stocks.

00:12:16.172 --> 00:12:18.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But about the middle of the night,

00:12:18.675 --> 00:12:20.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Paul and Silas were praying

00:12:20.760 --> 00:12:23.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and praising God with song,

00:12:23.930 --> 00:12:26.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the prisoners were listening to them.”

00:12:28.727 --> 00:12:30.937 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you think made them want to sing?

00:12:34.899 --> 00:12:36.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
They loved Jehovah.

00:12:36.651 --> 00:12:39.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when they focused on that,
how do you think they felt?

00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:46.578 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think

00:12:49.122 --> 00:12:51.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
they felt some peace.

00:12:51.166 --> 00:12:52.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right.

00:12:53.418 --> 00:12:55.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
How about we dig a little bit deeper?

00:12:56.546 --> 00:12:57.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:12:57.255 --> 00:12:57.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:13:03.386 --> 00:13:05.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what did you notice?

00:13:06.514 --> 00:13:10.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gabe and Olivia are under pressure

00:13:10.518 --> 00:13:15.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Olivia in the classroom,
Gabe at the witnessing cart.

00:13:16.524 --> 00:13:19.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
How will they handle the pressure

00:13:19.819 --> 00:13:24.074 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a way that preserves
their peace with Jehovah?

00:13:25.158 --> 00:13:27.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s a good question.

00:13:27.827 --> 00:13:30.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
And really, all of us

00:13:30.622 --> 00:13:33.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
need to reflect on that question

00:13:33.416 --> 00:13:36.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we’re under pressure.

00:13:36.086 --> 00:13:39.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that Jehovah’s way is the best way.

00:13:39.297 --> 00:13:43.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re convinced that his way of ruling
is the best way.

00:13:45.929 --> 00:13:48.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
But when we’re subjected to pressure,

00:13:48.890 --> 00:13:53.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
perhaps the victim of some injustice

00:13:53.561 --> 00:13:55.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
or even of some evil,

00:13:57.524 --> 00:14:02.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
we may be inclined
to take matters into our own hands.

00:14:03.988 --> 00:14:06.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when we do,

00:14:06.991 --> 00:14:10.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
it can jeopardize our peace.

00:14:11.663 --> 00:14:15.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how do we demonstrate respect

00:14:15.917 --> 00:14:18.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
for Jehovah’s sovereignty?

00:14:18.628 --> 00:14:22.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
The inspired advice
in Romans chapter 12 can help.

00:14:22.757 --> 00:14:26.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look together at Romans chapter 12,

00:14:26.094 --> 00:14:28.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
beginning in verse 17:

00:14:31.766 --> 00:14:35.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return evil for evil to no one.”

00:14:35.437 --> 00:14:40.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this provides the context
for what follows.

00:14:40.442 --> 00:14:43.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may suffer some evil.

00:14:43.570 --> 00:14:46.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return evil for evil to no one.

00:14:46.823 --> 00:14:51.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
Take into consideration what is fine
from the viewpoint of all men.”

00:14:51.703 --> 00:14:54.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then notice verse 18:

00:14:54.164 --> 00:14:57.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If possible, as far as it depends

00:14:57.208 --> 00:14:59.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
“on you,

00:14:59.753 --> 00:15:04.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
be peaceable (be a peacemaker)
with all men.”

00:15:06.593 --> 00:15:08.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, these words

00:15:08.636 --> 00:15:11.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
really heighten our appreciation

00:15:11.765 --> 00:15:15.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
for Jehovah’s reasonableness.

00:15:15.226 --> 00:15:18.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why do we say that?

00:15:18.104 --> 00:15:20.148 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because Jehovah doesn’t ask us

00:15:20.148 --> 00:15:24.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
to do something that we can’t do.

00:15:24.068 --> 00:15:27.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
He doesn’t ask us to control others.

00:15:27.864 --> 00:15:29.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
No,

00:15:30.867 --> 00:15:35.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the extent “it depends on you.”

00:15:35.914 --> 00:15:38.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah asks that each of us

00:15:38.583 --> 00:15:41.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
control ourselves,

00:15:41.169 --> 00:15:46.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
our response to a situation,

00:15:46.049 --> 00:15:48.134 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to be peacemakers.

00:15:49.469 --> 00:15:54.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then an explanation, verse 19:

00:15:54.182 --> 00:15:57.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not avenge yourselves, beloved,

00:15:57.769 --> 00:16:00.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
but yield place to the wrath.”

00:16:00.271 --> 00:16:01.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:16:01.231 --> 00:16:05.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For it is written: ‘Vengeance is mine;

00:16:05.109 --> 00:16:08.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
I will repay,’ says Jehovah.”

00:16:09.656 --> 00:16:12.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the advice is this:

00:16:12.158 --> 00:16:14.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be a peacemaker,

00:16:14.285 --> 00:16:16.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
and leave wrath to God.

00:16:16.788 --> 00:16:21.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let him determine
if and when and upon whom

00:16:21.417 --> 00:16:23.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
vengeance will be brought.

00:16:25.380 --> 00:16:27.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s easy to say,

00:16:27.674 --> 00:16:31.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
but is it always easy to do?

00:16:31.094 --> 00:16:33.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:16:33.096 --> 00:16:35.306 line:90% position:50% align:center
The example of King David

00:16:35.306 --> 00:16:38.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
can be very helpful to us.

00:16:38.768 --> 00:16:40.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
Through no fault of his own,

00:16:40.770 --> 00:16:43.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
David became the target

00:16:43.773 --> 00:16:48.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
of King Saul’s murderous hatred.

00:16:48.111 --> 00:16:50.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
And on several occasions,

00:16:50.321 --> 00:16:53.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
Saul tried to kill David.

00:16:53.658 --> 00:16:56.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
For several years David lived as a fugitive.

00:16:56.536 --> 00:17:00.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there were opportunities during that time

00:17:00.582 --> 00:17:05.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
for David to harm Saul, even to kill him.

00:17:06.671 --> 00:17:10.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
He could have justified that in his mind.

00:17:10.592 --> 00:17:13.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do you think had he done so

00:17:13.177 --> 00:17:17.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
it would have threatened his peace

00:17:17.098 --> 00:17:20.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his peace, especially, with Jehovah?

00:17:20.852 --> 00:17:24.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that it would.

00:17:24.063 --> 00:17:27.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how did David respond?

00:17:27.066 --> 00:17:29.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
On one occasion, he said to his men:

00:17:29.944 --> 00:17:34.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It is unthinkable from Jehovah’s standpoint

00:17:34.282 --> 00:17:36.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that I should do such a thing to my lord,

00:17:36.993 --> 00:17:39.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
the anointed of Jehovah.”

00:17:41.664 --> 00:17:44.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
What helped David?

00:17:44.459 --> 00:17:46.920 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, he saw a bigger picture

00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:50.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
than David and Saul, didn’t he?

00:17:50.298 --> 00:17:53.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
He saw a picture with David, Saul,

00:17:53.718 --> 00:17:55.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jehovah.

00:17:55.762 --> 00:17:59.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knew that if Saul needed to be corrected,

00:17:59.307 --> 00:18:03.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah would do it in his time and way.

00:18:03.478 --> 00:18:06.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result, David was willing to be patient

00:18:06.397 --> 00:18:08.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he preserved his peace

00:18:08.983 --> 00:18:12.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his peace with God, his inner peace,

00:18:12.820 --> 00:18:15.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his peace with those around him.

00:18:15.698 --> 00:18:18.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a beautiful example!

00:18:18.284 --> 00:18:21.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can be sure that if we demonstrate

00:18:21.621 --> 00:18:23.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
our love for Jehovah

00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:28.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
by respecting his sovereignty
and waiting on him,

00:18:28.670 --> 00:18:31.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will enjoy peace as well.

00:18:33.132 --> 00:18:35.134 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah assures us

00:18:35.134 --> 00:18:38.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he will bless his people

00:18:38.262 --> 00:18:41.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he will bless us with peace.

00:18:41.599 --> 00:18:44.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let us be determined to love Jehovah

00:18:44.227 --> 00:18:47.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our whole heart, soul, and mind

00:18:47.939 --> 00:18:51.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to demonstrate our love for Jehovah

00:18:51.067 --> 00:18:55.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
by patiently waiting on him
and respecting his sovereignty

00:18:55.697 --> 00:18:57.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his way of doing things.

00:18:57.740 --> 00:18:59.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we do, we will enjoy

00:18:59.951 --> 00:19:03.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
the incomparable peace of God.

00:19:04.539 --> 00:19:08.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Brother Ralph Walls,
a helper to the Personnel Committee,

00:19:08.668 --> 00:19:12.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
will present the next talk of this symposium,

00:19:12.171 --> 00:19:17.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace
—Love of Neighbor.”

